sentence: raymond alan duke friday, june 5, 2015| of raymond duke.
raymond alan duke, 52, of syracuse passed away friday.
born in syracuse, he was genuine and well liked by everyone he met. he will be greatly missed.
survivors: daughter, kayla george; son, rayven george; mother, doris duke; sisters, betty hamilton of st.
charles, la, marcia horine, karen duke of wood river junction, ri, debra duke; brother, james duke; many nieces, nephews, aunts, uncles, and cousins.
services: a prayer service and calling hour will from 10 a. m. to 11 a. m. friday at tindall funeral home, 1921 w genesee street.
burial will follow in greenlawn cemetery, warners.
